I started by exploring the application's **Feedback** section we already know vulnerable. Upon loading the feedback page I noticed a `returnPath` parameter in the URL ( set to `returnPath=/`)

Using the  debugger I found the script responsible for handling this parameter:

```jsx
$(function() {$('#backLink').attr("href", (new URLSearchParams(window.location.search)).get('returnPath'));});
```

**Technical Breakdown:**The script waits for the page to load, finds an element with the ID `backLink` (the "Back" button), and reads the value of `returnPath` from the URL. It then directly injects this value into the `href` attribute of that link using jQuery’s `.attr()` method.

